{"parse":{"title":"Terokkar Forest","pageid":32555,"wikitext":{"*":"{{Stub/Lore}}\n{{Infobox zone\n|ss=terokkar.jpg\n|name=Terokkar Forest\n|ruler=[[Terokk]]\n|pop=Unknown\n|affiliation=[[Skettis]]\n|capital=[[Shattrath City]]\n|races={{RaceIconExt|Arakkoa|Small}} [[Arakkoa]]<br/>{{Race|Draenei }}<br/>{{Race|Undead }}<br/>{{Race|Blood Elf }}<br/>{{Race|Human }}<br/>{{Race|High Elf }}<br/>{{Race|Orc }}<br/>{{Race|Fel Orc }}<br/>\n{{Race|Ethereal }}<br/>{{Race|Broken Draenei }}<br />{{RaceIconExt|LostOne|Small}} [[Draenei Lost Ones|Lost Ones]]<br/>{{Race|Ogre}}<br/>{{Race|Sand Gnome}}\n|loc=Southern [[Outland]]\n|major=[[Skettis]]<br/>[[Allerian Stronghold]]<br/>[[Stonebreaker Hold]]<br/>[[Firewing Point]]\n|level=62-80\n}}\n\n'''Terokkar Forest''' is a zone in [[Outland]] located east of [[Nagrand]], west of [[Shadowmoon Valley]], southeast of [[Zangarmarsh]], and southwest of [[Hellfire Peninsula]]. This forest was most likely named after [[Terokk]], an [[arakkoa]] demigod of some sort.\n\nTerokkar was seen as the [[Bone Wastes]] in previous maps and lore sources, but the Bone Wastes themselves are now a sub-region within the Terokkar Forest zone (in fact probably not the same Bone Wastes, as the current one was created only two years ago, according to ingame lore). Maybe one of the \"[[Green Havens]]\" replanted by druids to be like it was before the Horde necromancy and fel magic corrupted the land.\n\n== History ==\nTerokkar is most famous for the [[Bone Wastes]] and the ruined fortress of [[Auchindoun]].\n\nWorldofwarcraft.com says the following about the Terokkar Forest:\n\n''New hope has come to this ancient forest. Aided by the benevolent naaru, a group of draenei has rebuilt Shattrath City. The city has since thrown open its doors to welcome refugees of many different races from all over Outland. Yet the past has not left this area unmarked. To this day, only adventurers and graverobbers visit the haunted subterranean ruins of [[Auchindoun]].''\n\n== Geography ==\nThe flora consists of mostly dark green forest vegetation of crystal pines known as olemba trees. [[Shattrath City]] lies in the northwestern portion of zone. Alliance and Horde each have a town.<br />\n\nThe multi-winged instance [[Auchindoun]] can be found in this zone, containing four separate 5-man dungeons. There are no raid dungeons, micro dungeons, battlegrounds, or arenas in this zone. The spirit towers of the [[Bone Wastes]] provide a world PvP opportunity.\n\nEvery so often you can hear a roar while near Auchindoun - this is [[Teribus the Cursed]], flying in circles around Auchindoun.\n\n=== Maps and subregions ===\n[[Image:WorldMap-TerokkarForest.jpg|thumb|300px|left|Map of Terokkar Forest]]\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n!{{wow-inline}} In-game\n|-\n|{{Terokkar Forest|subzonesonly=}}\n|}\n{{clrl}}\n\n=== Dungeons ===\n[[File:Terokkar Forest.jpg|thumb|Terokkar Forest]]\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n! Dungeon Name \n! Level Range \n! Group Size\n! Approximate Run Time\n|-\n| {{portal|Mana-Tombs|bc}}  || 64-66\n| 5-man\n| 1.5-3 hours\n|-\n| {{portal|Auchenai Crypts|bc}}  || 65-67\n| 5-man\n| 2 hours\n|-\n| {{portal|Sethekk Halls|bc}}  || 67-69\n| 5-man\n| 1.5 hours-2 hours\n|-\n| {{portal|Shadow Labyrinth|bc}}  || 70-72\n| 5-man\n| 1.5 hours- 3 hours\n|}\n\n=== World PvP ===\n* [[Bone Wastes]]: In the Bone Wastes to the south, surrounding the ruins of [[Auchindoun]], there are five Spirit Towers. These spirit towers can be captured by players who are PvP flagged. If all five towers become captured by a single faction, that faction gets a zone-wide [[Blessing of Auchindoun]] aura ([[buff]]) which lasts for six hours. The aura gives +5% Damage, +5% Experience Gain, and the ability to create a {{loot|common|Spirit Shard}} in the [[Auchindoun]] instance. Spirit Shards can be spent at {{NPC|Horde|Spirit Sage Gartok}} at [[Stonebreaker Hold]] or {{NPC|Alliance|Spirit Sage Zran}} at [[Allerian Stronghold]].\n[[Image:TerokkarForest.jpg|450px|thumb|Concept art of the Terokkar Forest.]]\n=== Travel hubs ===\n;{{Alliance Icon Small}} [[Allerian Stronghold]]\n\n;{{Horde Icon Small}} [[Stonebreaker Hold]]\n\n;{{Neutral Icon Small}} [[Shattrath City]]\n\n=== Adjacent regions===\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Zone Name !! Faction !! Level Range !! Direction !! Access\n|-\n| [[Hellfire Peninsula]]\n| {{Alliance Icon Small}}{{Horde Icon Small}}\n| 58-63 || Northeast || Normal\n|-\n| [[Zangarmarsh]]\n| {{Alliance Icon Small}}{{Horde Icon Small}}\n| 60-64 || Northwest || Normal\n|-\n| [[Nagrand]]\n| {{Alliance Icon Small}}{{Horde Icon Small}}\n| 64-67 || West || Normal\n|-\n| [[Shadowmoon Valley]]\n| {{Alliance Icon Small}}{{Horde Icon Small}}\n| 67-70 || East || Normal\n|}\n\n== Notable characters ==\n[[File:Terokkar Forest concept.jpg|thumb|Concept art]]\n{{main|Terokkar Forest NPCs}}\n{{Stub/NPC}}\nArchmage [[Khadgar]] resides in [[Shattrath City]] and can be found in its center.\n\n== Quests ==\n{{main|Terokkar Forest quests}}\n{{seealso|Terokkar Forest questing guide}}\n\n{{Stub/Quest}}\n\n== Resources ==\n[[Image:TerokkarConcept.jpg|thumb|450px|Concept art of the Terokkar Forest.]]\n* [[Herb]]s\n** [[Dreaming Glory]]\n** [[Terocone]]\n** [[Felweed]]\n* [[Leather]]\n** [[Knothide Leather Scraps]]\n** [[Knothide Leather]]\n** [[Fel Hide]]\n* [[Ore]]\n** [[Fel Iron Ore]]\n** [[Adamantite Ore]]\n** [[Khorium Ore]]\n** [[Eternium Ore]]\n\n== Wild creatures\u00a0 ==\n{{col-begin}}{{col-3}}\n* [[Ancient]]s\n* [[Arakkoa]]\n* [[Basilisk]]s\n* [[Blood elves]]\n* [[Broken]]\n* [[Burrower]]s\n* [[Carrion bird]]s\n* [[Clefthoof]]s\n* [[Eredar]]\n* [[Ethereal]]s\n{{col-3}}\n* [[Fel Orc]]s\n* [[Frost Wyrm]]\n* [[Ghost]]s\n* [[Lost One]]s\n* [[Moth]]s\n* [[Owl]]s\n* [[Saber]]s\n* [[Sand Gnome]]s\n* [[Scorpid]]s\n* [[Shade]]s\n{{col-3}}\n* [[Skeleton]]s\n* [[Spider]]s\n* [[Treant]]s\n* [[Undead]]\n* [[Warp Stalker]]s\n* [[Water Elemental]]s\n* [[Wolves]]\n* [[Zombie]]s\n{{col-end}}\n\n== Trivia ==\n*The virtual version of the band [[Level 80 Elite Tauren Chieftain]] performs on Terokkar Forest at the [[Darkmoon Faire]]<ref>[[File:ETC.jpg|30px]]</ref> and in the [[World's End Tavern]] every three hours, added with the [[Patch 2.4.3 (undocumented changes)|Patch 2.4.3]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== See also==\n* [[Server:Terokkar US]]\n* [[Server:Terokkar Europe]]\n\n== External links ==\n{{elinks-zone|3519}}\n\n\n{{Terokkar Forest}}\n{{Outland}}\n\n[[es:Terokkar Forest]]\n[[fr:For\u00eat de Terokkar]]\n[[ja:Terokkar Forest]]\n[[pl:Terokkar Forest]]\n[[ru:\u041b\u0435\u0441 \u0422\u0435\u0440\u043e\u043a\u043a\u0430\u0440]]\n[[Category:Forests]]\n[[Category:Outland]]\n[[Category:Terokkar Forest| ]]\n[[Category:Woods]]"}}}